                <tr>
                  <td
 style="background-color: rgb(204, 204, 255); vertical-align: top;"><!--HIDEME-->Prerequisites,
Download and Installation:
                  <br>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td style="border-style: none; vertical-align:
		  top;"><!--HIDEME-->

<!--HIDEME-->Download the latest version of Aline here: <a href="aline_011208.tar.gz"><!--HIDEME-->[tar-gzip]
                  </a><!--HIDEME--> or
                  <a name="DL" href="aline_011208.tar.bz2"><span
 style="text-decoration: underline;"><!--HIDEME-->[tar-bzip2]
                  </span>                  </a><!--HIDEME--> or
                  <a href="aline_011208.zip"><span
 style="text-decoration: underline;"><!--HIDEME-->[zip]
                  </span></a><br>

Aline is a perl program requiring perl 5.8 and the Tk module. </p>
Perl: Recent linux and MacOSX distributions include perl/Tk so you should be ready to go. See below for generic instructions for installing the perl Tk module in an existing perl installation.<br>
If you have trouble with perl/Tk on MacOSX and have fink installed, please try 'fink install tk-pm588'. (Thanks to Andreas FÃ¶rster (Imperial) for the tip).<br> 
If you have trouble with perl (and especially if you use windows), you can install the free <a href=http://www.activestate.com/Products/activeperl/>ActivePerl</a> distribution (use version 5.8 rather than 5.10 as the latter does not currently (08-01-2008) include Tk) and this should solve those problems.
If you have insurmountable problems under Windows, Aline will also work under the <a href=http://cygwin.com/>CygWIN<a/> environment (you need to ensure that perltk, xorg-x11-base and gs are selected for installation).


<h3>Brief Instructions</h3>
Windows:<br>
(1) Ensure <a href=http://www.activestate.com/Products/activeperl/>ActivePerl</a> is installed (see above).<br>
(2) Download and unzip the <a href=aline_011208.zip>zip file</a>.<br>
(3) Open the "aline"->"bin" folder and double-click "aline.pl" (or "aline" with the ActivePerl logo).<br>
<br>
Unix/MacOSX:<br>
(1) Open a terminal window<br>
(2) Download the <a href=aline_011208.tar.bz2>bzip2</a> or <a href=aline_011208.tar.gz>gzip</a> file.<br>
<!--HIDEME-->
(3) Unpack somewhere: e.g.
                  <br>
                  <span style="font-family: monospace;"><!--HIDEME-->cd
/programs/
                  </span><br style="font-family: monospace;">
                  <span style="font-family: monospace;"><!--HIDEME-->gzip
-dc /downloads/aline.tar.gz | tar -xvf -
                  </span><br style="font-family: monospace;">
(4a) Setup use for tcsh/csh users: (type 'echo $SHELL' to find out which shell you use)<br> 
                  <span style="font-family: monospace;"><!--HIDEME-->setenv
ALINEHOME /programs/aline </span><br style="font-family: monospace;">
                  <span style="font-family: monospace;"><!--HIDEME-->set
path = ($path $ALINEHOME/bin)
                  </span><br>
                  <span style="font-family: monospace;"><!--HIDEME-->
rehash
                  </span><br>
<!--HIDEME-->The 'setenv' and 'set path' lines can be added to your ~/.tcshrc or ~/.cshrc file to automatically setup aline when you log in<br>
(4b) Setup use for bash users: (type 'echo $SHELL' to find out which shell you use)<br>
                  <span style="font-family: monospace;"><!--HIDEME-->
ALINEHOME=/programs/aline ; export $ALINEHOME</span><br style="font-family: monospace;">
                  <span style="font-family: monospace;"><!--HIDEME-->set
PATH=$path:$ALINEHOME/bin ; EXPORT $PATH
                  </span><br>
<!--HIDEME-->The 'ALINEHOME' and 'PATH' lines can be added to your ~/.bashrc file to automatically setup aline when you log in<br>
<br>
(5) Type 'aline' and start playing.


To get full functionality, a number of accessory programs are desireable:<br>
<ul>
<li>Ghostscript (commonly installed on linux/MacOSX - type 'gs' in a terminal to test), otherwise see if it is available as part of your system or go to <a href=http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~ghost/>http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~ghost/</a><br></li>
<li>wget <a
href="http://www.gnu.org/software/wget/">http://www.gnu.org/software/wget/</a>
- already there with most linux/osx. Make sure 'wget' is in your path.</li>
<li>DSSP <a href="http://swift.cmbi.ru.nl/gv/dssp/">http://swift.cmbi.ru.nl/gv/dssp/</a>:
install and make sure 'dssp' is in your path.</li>
<li>CLUSTALW <a href="ftp://ftp-igbmc.u-strasbg.fr/pub/ClustalW">ftp://ftp-igbmc.u-strasbg.fr/pub/ClustalW//</a>:
install and make sure 'clustalw' is in your path.</li>
<li>CHAINSAW <a
href="http://www.ccp4.ac.uk/ccp4/html/chainsaw.html">http://www.ccp4.ac.uk/ccp4/html/chainsaw.html</a>
- part of the CCP4 suite. Install CCP4 and make sure 'chainsaw' is in your path.
</li></ul>
                  <br>

</td></tr>
                <tr>
                  <td
 style="background-color: rgb(204, 204, 255); vertical-align:
                  top;"><!--HIDEME--><a name="perl"></a>Installing perl and its modules
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td style="border-style: none; vertical-align:
		  top;"><!--HIDEME-->
NOTE:If you have problems with perl prerequisites (compilation, installing etc), please consider using ActivePerl (see above).
To install additional modules using a prexisting perl version you must have superuser or root privileges. In principal, the Tk module can be installed by issuing the command "perl -MCPAN -e 'install Tk'". However, as Tk provides a graphical user interface, the X display must be set up to allow windows to be created during the build process, so it may be necessary to login as root via ssh ('ssh -X root@localhost') rather than '/bin/su -'.
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
